-- Bahrain to meet investors ahead of potential sovereign bond - leads
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 10:00AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Aug 28 (Reuters) - Bahrain has chosen four banks to arrange investor meetings before a potential long-dated sovereign bond issue, a document from lead managers said on Thursday.

The Gulf Arab state has chosen Citigroup <C.N>, Gulf International Bank [GLFBK.UL], Mitsubishi UFJ <8306.T> and Standard Chartered <STAN.L> to arrange the roadshows which will begin on Sept. 2, according to the document.